    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="16"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d16">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName type="from">Churchill</persName> to
                        President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d16fn1">Sent to Washington by the United States Naval
                        Attaché, London, via Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-29">April 29,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FNP1">Former Naval Person</gloss> to President, Personal and
                    Secret Number 291.</p>
                <p>It seems to me most necessary that we should all settle together now first <gloss
                        target="#t_Husky1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Husky</hi>
                    </gloss> and exploitation thereof and secondly the future of <gloss
                        target="#t_Anakim1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Anakim</hi>
                    </gloss> in light of Burma campaign experiences and shipping stringency. There
                    are also a number of other burning questions which you and I could with
                    advantage bring up to date.</p>
                <p>I think I could manage to be with you by Tuesday 11th May. I would bring Wavell,
                    Peirse and Admiral Somerville as well as Pound, Brooke, Portal, Mountbatten and
                    Leathers. Please say whether you <pb facs="0118" n="16" xml:id="pg_16"/> would
                    like this or whether you would prefer to send your people over here which of
                    course would be easier for us.</p>
            </div>
